OWASP : Open Web Application Security Project
OWASP TOP 10
1. Injection
    - Untrusted/Invalidated data is sent to server.
2. Broken Authentication
    - Involved authentication and session management 
    - Items such as passwords, keys, session token
3. Sensitive Data Exposure
    - Do not properly protect sensitive data 
    - Encryption at rest / in transit
4. XML External Entities
    - Older and poorly configured XML 
    - URI handler, internal file shares, internal port scanning, remote code execution and ddos
5. Broken Access Control
    - Access unauthorized functionality / data
    - Allow user bew sensitive files, modify other data, change access right.
6. Security MisConfiguration
7. Cross Site Scripting
8. Insecure Deserialization
9. Using Components with known vulnerabilities
10.Insufficient Logging & Monitoring
